olive oil
2 potato
½ Onion
1 packet green beans
1 carrot
1 packet chicken thigh
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
½ packet cream
40 g butter
2 tbs milk
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder

• Boil the kettle. Cut potato into large chunks (peel if you prefer!). Thinly slice onion (see ingredients). Trim green beans. Thinly slice carrot into sticks.
• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water, then add a generous pinch of salt. Cook potato in the boiling water, over high heat, until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes.
• In last 8 minutes of cook time, place a colander or steamer basket on top, then add green beans and carrots. Cover and steam until tender and potatoes can be easily pierced with a fork, 7-8 minutes.
• Transfer green beans and carrots to a bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then set aside and cover to keep warm.
• Drain potatoes and return to the saucepan.

• Meanwhile, cut chicken thigh into 2cm chunks.
• In large frying pan, heat drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook chicken, Nan’s special seasoning and onion, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add cream (see ingredients) and cook until thickened, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove from heat, then season to taste and set aside.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it’s no longer pink inside.

• Add the butter, milk and chicken-style stock powder to the potato. Mash until smooth.

• Divide potato mash and steamed veggies between plates.
• Top with chicken and creamy onion sauce to serve. Enjoy!